# Re-run mic/AEC reconciliation whenever ALSA sound cards appear or
# disappear. The reconciler is intentionally cheap and idempotent:
# it only flips service/env state when the current mic config is one
# JTS owns (Array, udp:PORT, or a configured candidate). Custom
# JASPER_MIC_DEVICE values are left alone.
#
# This is deliberately keyed to sound control nodes rather than a
# hard-coded XVF USB id. Supported mic identity lives in the mic profile
# registry; JASPER_MIC_DEVICE_CANDIDATES remains only the direct-mic
# fallback hint. The policy stays in the reconciler.

ACTION=="add|remove", SUBSYSTEM=="sound", KERNEL=="controlC*", TAG+="systemd", ENV{SYSTEMD_WANTS}+="jasper-aec-reconcile.service"
